TankPilot Phase 5 – TankPilot Connect

Vision

TankPilot begins as the world’s smartest virtual fuel gauge.

With an OBD-II adapter connected, it evolves into a living digital twin of the user’s vehicle.

Objectives

Unlock advanced features when live telemetry is available.

The transition should feel seamless.

Display a subtle badge:

“TankPilot Connect Active”

Digital Twin

Create a persistent vehicle profile that learns over time.

Track:

* Learned city MPG
* Learned highway MPG
* Seasonal fuel economy
* Idle fuel consumption
* Typical driving style
* Fill-up consistency
* Average trip length
* Engine runtime
* Lifetime fuel purchased
* Lifetime fuel cost
* Maintenance history

Every vehicle becomes unique over time.

Vehicle Health

Add a Vehicle Health section containing:

* Oil change reminders
* Tire rotation reminders
* Air filter reminders
* Battery health
* Maintenance timeline
* Service history
* Receipt scanning (future-ready)
* Diagnostic trouble codes
* Check Engine Light status

AI Insights

Generate helpful observations such as:

* Fuel economy has declined over the past month.
* Increased idle time is affecting fuel efficiency.
* Average MPG improved after the last maintenance event.
* Oil change is approaching based on mileage.
* Battery voltage appears lower than normal.

Never fabricate diagnostics.

Only generate insights supported by available data.

Long-Term Goal

TankPilot should feel less like a fuel tracker and more like an intelligent operating system for the user’s vehicle.

The digital twin should become increasingly personalized with every trip, every fill-up, and every maintenance event.
